00:24:24,905 --> 00:24:25,947
No.

254
00:24:27,950 --> 00:24:28,950
L like your pin.

255
00:24:30,160 --> 00:24:32,286
L was wondering that myself.

256
00:24:33,789 --> 00:24:36,290
Would you want to maybe, possibly,

257
00:24:36,833 --> 00:24:40,336
sometime go out
for some pizza or something?

258
00:24:40,587 --> 00:24:42,046
Like, Friday?

259
00:24:43,173 --> 00:24:44,507
- Saturday?
- L can't.

260
00:24:44,591 --> 00:24:46,551
Sunday, Monday, Tuesday?

261
00:24:50,973 --> 00:24:53,641
- We have finals tomorrow.
- Yeah, I know.

262
00:24:54,810 --> 00:24:57,311
Lf we don't go now, it won't happen.

263
00:24:58,313 --> 00:25:01,857
Do you understand?
So what do you want to do?

264
00:25:36,351 --> 00:25:39,020
Please keep your hands inside the car!

265
00:25:56,330 --> 00:25:58,789
This is my favorite pizza place.

266
00:25:58,874 --> 00:25:59,915
Tony!

267
00:26:00,042 --> 00:26:02,043
One large, extra plankton.

268
00:26:02,794 --> 00:26:06,172
We have so little time.
They're going to be here any minute.

269
00:26:06,298 --> 00:26:09,216
- Who are?
- They don't want me talking to you.

270
00:26:09,718 --> 00:26:11,344
Then don't talk.

271
00:26:25,567 --> 00:26:27,068
They're here.

272
00:26:28,362 --> 00:26:29,904
- Truman.
- What do they want?

273
00:26:29,988 --> 00:26:32,114
Listen to me.
Everybody knows about you.

274
00:26:32,199 --> 00:26:33,908
Everybody knows everything you do.

275
00:26:33,992 --> 00:26:35,993
They're pretending, Truman.
Do you understand?

276
00:26:36,078 --> 00:26:37,679
- Everybody's pretending.
- L don't know.

277
00:26:37,746 --> 00:26:39,664
No, my name's not Lauren. lt's Sylvia.

278
00:26:39,748 --> 00:26:41,040
- My name's Sylvia.
- Sylvia?

279
00:26:41,124 --> 00:26:43,501
- Yeah.
- Lauren, sweetheart, not again.

280
00:26:43,585 --> 00:26:46,504
- Wait a minute. Who are you?
- L'm her father.

281
00:26:46,755 --> 00:26:49,507
- l've never even seen him before.
- We weren't doing anything.

282
00:26:49,591 --> 00:26:52,343
He's lying.
Truman, please don't listen to him.

283
00:26:52,427 --> 00:26:57,181
Everything l've told you is the truth.
This, it's fake. lt's all for you.

284
00:26:57,265 --> 00:27:00,101
- l don't understand.
- The sky and sea, everything, it's a set.

285
00:27:00,185 --> 00:27:01,185
Lt's a show.

286
00:27:01,269 --> 00:27:03,646
Everybody's watching you.
Please don't listen to him.

287
00:27:03,730 --> 00:27:05,856
He's going to lie to you.
They're watching us now.

288
00:27:05,941 --> 00:27:08,943
- l want to know what's going on.
- Schizophrenia. She has episodes.

289
00:27:09,027 --> 00:27:10,361
We've tried everything.

290
00:27:10,445 --> 00:27:13,781
Hypnotism, shock therapy. Don't worry.

291
00:27:13,865 --> 00:27:15,908
- Truman!
- You're not the first.

292
00:27:15,992 --> 00:27:19,370
You're not the first. She brings
all her boyfriends down here.

293
00:27:19,454 --> 00:27:22,039
What's he saying? Truman, he's lying.

294
00:27:22,958 --> 00:27:25,292
- Get out of here. Come and find me.
- Don't worry.

295
00:27:25,377 --> 00:27:28,838
We're going to Fiji.
Fiji. We're moving to Fiji.

296
00:27:28,922 --> 00:27:30,005
Fiji?

297
00:27:41,977 --> 00:27:43,185
Sylvia!

298
00:27:43,270 --> 00:27:44,270
Hey!

299
00:27:53,864 --> 00:27:56,323
Why didn't he just follow her to Fiji?

300
00:27:56,408 --> 00:28:00,870
His mother got sick, really sick.
He couldn't leave her. He's kind.

301
00:28:00,954 --> 00:28:02,705
Maybe he's too kind.

302
00:28:03,290 --> 00:28:05,916
L can't believe he married Meryl
on the rebound.

303
00:28:06,001 --> 00:28:07,334
Excuse me.

304
00:28:07,461 --> 00:28:08,711
Come on, Sal.

305
00:28:08,795 --> 00:28:11,881
We've already got this
on the greatest hits tape.

306
00:28:11,965 --> 00:28:13,007
Can I borrow that?

307
00:29:00,055 --> 00:29:01,972
Close, but no cigar.

308
00:29:30,335 --> 00:29:33,003
And it's another beautiful day
in paradise, folks,

309
00:29:33,088 --> 00:29:35,840
but don't forget to buckle up
out there in radioland.

310
00:29:35,924 --> 00:29:38,050
Remember, a good driver...

311
00:29:46,893 --> 00:29:48,519
wait for the cue.

312
00:29:50,313 --> 00:29:51,814
Stand by, one.

313
00:29:52,440 --> 00:29:54,233
Countdown to action.

314
00:29:54,359 --> 00:29:55,860
Stand by, one.

315
00:29:58,864 --> 00:30:01,907
He's heading west on Stewart.
Stand by, all extras.

316
00:30:01,992 --> 00:30:06,328
He'll be on you in about 90 seconds.
Props, make sure the coffee's hot.

317
00:30:06,454 --> 00:30:09,623
Okay, he's making his turn
onto Lancaster Square.

318
00:30:12,210 --> 00:30:13,961
Oh, my God! He nearly hit her.

319
00:30:14,045 --> 00:30:16,213
Something's wrong.
Change frequencies.

320
00:30:21,595 --> 00:30:23,304
Sorry about that, folks.

321
00:30:23,388 --> 00:30:25,723
L guess we picked up
a police frequency or something.

322
00:30:25,807 --> 00:30:28,726
Lt sometimes happens,
and it can drive you crazy.

323
00:30:28,810 --> 00:30:30,936
Okay, it's Classical Clive back in here

324
00:30:31,021 --> 00:30:33,564
and we've still got
some great music up ahead,

325
00:30:33,648 --> 00:30:34,899
but don't forget to buckle up.

326
00:30:34,983 --> 00:30:37,610
Remember safety.
A good driver is a safe driver.

327
00:30:37,694 --> 00:30:39,820
A safe driver is what? Yes...

328
00:30:55,795 --> 00:30:57,338
Morning, ma'am.

329
00:32:37,105 --> 00:32:39,440
- l love that idea.
- Lt's pretty cool, isn't it?

330
00:33:43,963 --> 00:33:45,172
Can I help?

331
00:33:45,256 --> 00:33:47,633
Yeah. I have an appointment
at Gable Enterprises.

332
00:33:47,717 --> 00:33:49,176
They went bust.

333
00:33:54,307 --> 00:33:56,391
- What's happening?
- Nothing.

334
00:33:56,476 --> 00:33:59,603
- Just tell me what's happening.
- Got to go, sir. We're remodeling.

335
00:33:59,687 --> 00:34:01,688
No, you're not.
What are those people doing?

336
00:34:01,773 --> 00:34:03,482
Lt's none of your business!

337
00:34:03,566 --> 00:34:06,026
Lf you don't tell me what's happening,
l'll report you!

338
00:34:06,111 --> 00:34:07,861
You're trespassing.

339
00:34:39,144 --> 00:34:40,352
Marlon.

340
00:34:40,895 --> 00:34:43,647
- Truman. What are you doing here?
- L got to talk to you.

341
00:34:43,731 --> 00:34:45,607
Lt's a bad time, okay? l'm way behind.

342
00:34:45,692 --> 00:34:48,235
L'm onto something, Marlon.
Something big.

343
00:34:48,361 --> 00:34:51,405
- You okay? You look like shit.
- L think l'm mixed up in something.

344
00:34:51,489 --> 00:34:52,531
Mixed up in what?

345
00:34:52,615 --> 00:34:54,366
There's no point trying to explain it,

346
00:34:54,450 --> 00:34:57,578
but a lot of strange things
have been happening.

347
00:35:00,957 --> 00:35:04,668
The people on the elevator.
There was no backing on it.

348
00:35:04,752 --> 00:35:07,296
L looked out. There was people there.

349
00:35:07,380 --> 00:35:10,591
And on the radio on the way to work,
it starts following me along,

350
00:35:10,675 --> 00:35:12,384
talking about everything that l'm doing.

351
00:35:12,468 --> 00:35:15,137
- Know what I mean?
- Truman, this is one of your fantasies...

352
00:35:15,221 --> 00:35:16,638
l think this is about my dad.

353
00:35:16,723 --> 00:35:18,932
- Your dad?
- L think he's alive.

354
00:35:19,767 --> 00:35:23,812
Yeah. I'll tell you about it later.
L'm definitely being followed.

355
00:35:24,272 --> 00:35:25,314
Who?

356
00:35:27,108 --> 00:35:30,569
Lt's hard to tell.
They look just like regular people.

357
00:35:33,907 --> 00:35:37,492
- How about those two?
- L don't know. Could be.

358
00:35:38,494 --> 00:35:42,289
Lt's when l'm unpredictable, that's...
They can't, you know.

359
00:35:43,625 --> 00:35:46,084
- Did anything happen?
- No.

360
00:35:46,544 --> 00:35:48,378
We gotta get out of here.
You ready to go?

361
00:35:48,463 --> 00:35:50,339
- No. I just came here.
- Come on.

362
00:35:50,423 --> 00:35:52,132
L told you I can't.

363
00:35:55,803 --> 00:35:58,305
You're going to get both our asses fired,
you know that?

364
00:35:58,389 --> 00:36:00,557
- Okay, man, let's do it.
- What?

365
00:36:00,642 --> 00:36:02,768
Whatever you say, l'm game.

366
00:36:02,852 --> 00:36:05,354
- What are you talking about?
- Yes, sirree.

367
00:36:05,480 --> 00:36:07,981
Your birthday comes but once a year.

368
00:36:11,069 --> 00:36:13,654
Maybe l'm being set up for something.

369
00:36:14,155 --> 00:36:15,906
You ever think about that, Marlon?

370
00:36:15,990 --> 00:36:19,076
Like your whole life
has been building toward something?

371
00:36:19,160 --> 00:36:20,160
No.

372
00:36:22,580 --> 00:36:25,207
When you were hauling chickens
in the summer for Kaiser,

373
00:36:25,291 --> 00:36:27,834
what was the furthest
you ever got off the island?

374
00:36:27,919 --> 00:36:31,380
Went all over.
Never found a place like this, though.

375
00:36:32,882 --> 00:36:35,717
Look at that sunset, Truman.
Lt's perfect.

376
00:36:36,594 --> 00:36:37,678
Yeah.

377
00:36:38,680 --> 00:36:40,389
That's the big guy.

378
00:36:41,266 --> 00:36:44,309
- Quite a paintbrush he's got.
- Yep.

379
00:36:48,439 --> 00:36:50,857
Just between you and me, Marlon,

380
00:36:52,402 --> 00:36:54,528
l'm going away for a while.

381
00:36:55,738 --> 00:36:58,031
- Really?
- Yeah.

382
00:37:00,034 --> 00:37:01,493
Little angel.

383
00:37:07,959 --> 00:37:09,543
My little clown.

384
00:37:11,796 --> 00:37:13,338
Old carrot top.

385
00:37:14,048 --> 00:37:15,716
The best of both of us.

386
00:37:17,510 --> 00:37:20,053
We should be
getting you home, Mother.

387
00:37:20,138 --> 00:37:23,598
Hold on a minute.
Here's us at Mt. Rushmore.

388
00:37:23,683 --> 00:37:25,976
Do you remember, Truman,
when Dad was still with us?

389
00:37:26,060 --> 00:37:29,521
That was quite a drive.
You slept the whole way there.

390
00:37:30,273 --> 00:37:31,898
Lt looks so small.

391
00:37:31,983 --> 00:37:34,234
Things always do
when you look back, darling.

392
00:37:34,319 --> 00:37:35,777
Look, Truman.

393
00:37:36,112 --> 00:37:38,655
The happiest day of our lives. Look.

394
00:37:41,326 --> 00:37:43,493
Jean, Jodie, Joanne.

395
00:37:43,578 --> 00:37:46,079
Doesn't she look beautiful, Truman?

396
00:37:47,040 --> 00:37:48,623
She still does.

397
00:37:48,708 --> 00:37:51,418
And there's lots of pages left over
for baby photos.

398
00:37:51,502 --> 00:37:55,088
L would like to hold a grandchild
in my arms before I go.

399
00:37:55,923 --> 00:37:57,841
Angela, we really should
be getting you home.

400
00:37:57,925 --> 00:38:00,427
- l'll take her.
- No. You stay, relax.

401
00:38:00,511 --> 00:38:02,220
Enjoy yourself.
Your favorite show will be coming on.

402
00:38:02,305 --> 00:38:03,347
You sure?

403
00:38:03,431 --> 00:38:05,349
Besides, we have something
to discuss.

404
00:38:06,309 --> 00:38:09,936
- A certain person's birthday.
- L see.

405
00:38:11,522 --> 00:38:15,025
And there'll be another episode of
l Love Lucy same time tomorrow.

406
00:38:15,109 --> 00:38:17,944
But right now,
it's time for Golden Oldies.

407
00:38:18,029 --> 00:38:20,697
Tonight, we present
the enduring, much-loved classic,

408
00:38:20,782 --> 00:38:22,866
Show Me the Way to Go Home.

409
00:38:22,950 --> 00:38:25,160
A hymn of praise to small-town life,

410
00:38:25,244 --> 00:38:27,537
where we learn
that you don't have to leave home

411
00:38:27,622 --> 00:38:32,250
to discover what the world's all about,
and that no one is poor who has friends.

412
00:38:32,877 --> 00:38:37,255
Full of laughter and love, pain and
sadness, but ultimately redemption,

413
00:38:37,340 --> 00:38:40,050
we share the trials and tribulations
of the Abbott family.

414
00:38:40,134 --> 00:38:43,053
Note the touching performance
of Ronald Brierly as Uncle Bunny.

415
00:38:43,137 --> 00:38:45,722
That scene with the bowl of cherries
is going to have you

416
00:38:45,807 --> 00:38:48,725
splitting your sides
with laughter all over again.

417
00:38:48,810 --> 00:38:52,771
And there'll be tears, too,
when David and Jennifer are reunited.

418
00:38:52,855 --> 00:38:56,691
But enough from me.
Let's join the Abbotts in Camden village.

419
00:39:24,053 --> 00:39:25,804
Thank you, sweetie.

420
00:39:29,684 --> 00:39:33,019
L need to talk to you,
but let's go outside.

421
00:39:33,813 --> 00:39:37,858
- Sweetie, l'd love to, but l'm really late.
- What's your rush?

422
00:39:39,068 --> 00:39:40,277
Surgery.

423
00:39:40,361 --> 00:39:43,822
There was that elevator disaster
downtown. lt was on the news last night.

424
00:39:43,906 --> 00:39:45,615
This cable just snapped.

425
00:39:45,700 --> 00:39:48,243
This elevator,
it just plummeted down 10 flights.

426
00:39:48,327 --> 00:39:50,787
The non-union workers. Just monsters.

427
00:39:50,872 --> 00:39:53,498
That building, it's right next door
to where you work.

428
00:39:53,583 --> 00:39:55,584
Can you imagine
if you had been in there?

429
00:39:55,668 --> 00:39:57,210
Lt's not even worth thinking about.

430
00:39:57,295 --> 00:40:00,213
Anyway, I have an amputation
on one of the young women

431
00:40:00,298 --> 00:40:03,800
who was in that elevator.
She's very young. lt's very sad.

432
00:40:03,885 --> 00:40:07,345
- Anyway, wish me luck.
- L'll cross my fingers for you.

433
00:40:49,639 --> 00:40:52,807
Excuse me. Hi. Excuse me.
May I help you?

434
00:40:54,477 --> 00:40:58,605
Yes. l'm looking for my wife,
Nurse Burbank. lt's very important.

435
00:40:58,689 --> 00:41:02,067
L'm afraid that that's not possible.
She's in pre-op.

436
00:41:02,860 --> 00:41:05,445
Sure. Okay, fine.

437
00:41:05,863 --> 00:41:08,532
- Can you pass along a message?
- L'll try.

438
00:41:08,616 --> 00:41:12,369
Can you tell her I had to go to Fiji,
and that I'll call her when I get there?

439
00:41:12,453 --> 00:41:16,122
- When you get to Fiji?
- You got it.

440
00:41:16,207 --> 00:41:19,668
- Fine. I'll tell her.
- Thank you so much.

441
00:41:46,445 --> 00:41:48,321
- Sorry.
- Lt's okay.

442
00:41:49,574 --> 00:41:51,908
Here, let me help you with that.

443
00:41:56,247 --> 00:41:57,581
He's here.

444
00:41:59,792 --> 00:42:01,001
L know.

445
00:42:02,003 --> 00:42:03,253
Scalpel.

446
00:42:09,927 --> 00:42:13,597
L'm now making my primary incision

447
00:42:14,223 --> 00:42:17,267
just above the right knee.

448
00:42:20,271 --> 00:42:21,271
Hold her.

449
00:42:22,356 --> 00:42:23,732
Nicely done.

450
00:42:24,275 --> 00:42:27,110
This isn't going to be pretty.
Unless you're family...

451
00:42:27,194 --> 00:42:29,696
lt's just beautiful. Beautiful job.

452
00:42:31,616 --> 00:42:34,200
L'll just let someone else tidy up here.

453
00:42:58,726 --> 00:43:01,227
- l'm sorry to keep you.
- That's okay.

454
00:43:03,272 --> 00:43:07,067
- How can I help?
- L would like to book a flight to Fiji.

455
00:43:09,236 --> 00:43:11,446
When would you like to leave?

456
00:43:12,406 --> 00:43:13,573
Today.

457
00:43:31,342 --> 00:43:34,969
L'm sorry. I don't have anything
for at least a month.

458
00:43:35,429 --> 00:43:37,931
- A month?
- Lt's the busy season.

459
00:43:40,226 --> 00:43:42,352
You want to book the flight?

460
00:43:43,187 --> 00:43:46,898
Lt doesn't matter.
L'll make other arrangements, okay?

461
00:43:50,111 --> 00:43:53,029
Last call for Chicago!

462
00:43:53,364 --> 00:43:55,782
All aboard!

463
00:44:00,913 --> 00:44:02,247
Thank you.

464
00:44:05,126 --> 00:44:07,127
Windy city, here we come.

465
00:44:09,255 --> 00:44:10,463
- Hi.
- Hi.

466
00:44:14,009 --> 00:44:15,802
Hello. Hi.

467
00:44:17,805 --> 00:44:18,847
Sisters.

468
00:44:18,931 --> 00:44:22,642
- Mom, isn't that...
- Face the front.

469
00:44:50,087 --> 00:44:52,589
Everybody off. We've got a problem.

470
00:45:12,151 --> 00:45:13,693
L'm sorry, son.

471
00:45:27,541 --> 00:45:30,251
His father was from Chicago,
wasn't he?

472
00:45:30,503 --> 00:45:34,214
No. His dentist was from Pensacola.
His father was from Des Moines.

473
00:45:34,298 --> 00:45:36,382
But how come he wants to go
to Chicago?

474
00:45:36,467 --> 00:45:39,093
He's not going to Chicago.
He's not going anywhere.

475
00:45:39,178 --> 00:45:41,262
He has to have it out with Meryl.

476
00:45:57,238 --> 00:45:58,404
Truman?

477
00:46:03,702 --> 00:46:06,913
- Honey, are you okay?
- Get in.

478
00:46:10,584 --> 00:46:11,793
Truman.

479
00:46:13,087 --> 00:46:14,212
Look.

480
00:46:17,800 --> 00:46:18,967
What?

481
00:46:20,135 --> 00:46:22,762
L predict that in just a moment,

482
00:46:24,431 --> 00:46:28,601
we will see a lady on a red bike,
followed by a man with flowers

483
00:46:29,562 --> 00:46:32,605
and a Volkswagen Beetle
with a dented fender.

484
00:46:32,940 --> 00:46:35,024
- Truman, please.
- Look.

485
00:46:40,823 --> 00:46:42,031
Lady,

486
00:46:43,534 --> 00:46:44,868
flowers,

487
00:46:46,579 --> 00:46:48,162
and...

488
00:46:50,624 --> 00:46:53,543
- Truman, this is silly.
- There it is!

489
00:46:53,627 --> 00:46:55,962
There's that dented Beetle! Yes!

490
00:47:03,345 --> 00:47:05,972
Don't you want to know how I did that?
L'll tell you.

491
00:47:06,056 --> 00:47:08,474
They're on a loop.
They go around the block.

492
00:47:08,559 --> 00:47:12,395
They come back. They go around again.
They just go round and round.

493
00:47:12,479 --> 00:47:13,855
Round and round.

494
00:47:13,939 --> 00:47:16,274
L invited Rita and Marlon
for a barbecue on Sunday.

495
00:47:16,358 --> 00:47:18,818
- l'm gonna make my potato salad.
- L won't be here Sunday.

496
00:47:18,903 --> 00:47:20,862
L need you to remind me
we need more charcoal.

497
00:47:20,946 --> 00:47:23,823
Are you listening to a word l'm saying?

