01:04:22,175 --> 01:04:25,302
Most effective. Truman's been
terrified of the water ever since.

750
01:04:25,386 --> 01:04:28,221
When Kirk read the synopsis
for the Death At Sea episode,

751
01:04:28,306 --> 01:04:31,767
he was disappointed, to say the least.

752
01:04:33,019 --> 01:04:35,437
L'm sure that's what caused him
to break back onto the set.

753
01:04:35,521 --> 01:04:38,857
But how do you intend to explain
his 22-year absence?

754
01:04:40,777 --> 01:04:43,070
- Amnesia.
- Brilliant.

755
01:04:43,863 --> 01:04:45,697
Let's take some viewer phone calls.

756
01:04:45,782 --> 01:04:48,700
Charlotte, North Carolina,
you're on with Christof.

757
01:04:49,786 --> 01:04:51,244
Yeah, hi, Christof.

758
01:04:51,537 --> 01:04:55,040
L was just wondering how many
cameras you got there in that town.

759
01:04:55,500 --> 01:04:57,626
Somewhere in the vicinity of 5,000.

760
01:04:58,044 --> 01:05:02,756
- That's a lot of cameras.
- Remember, we started with just one.

761
01:05:04,509 --> 01:05:06,551
He was curious from birth.

762
01:05:07,553 --> 01:05:11,181
Premature by two weeks. lt was almost
as if he couldn't wait to get started.

763
01:05:11,265 --> 01:05:13,558
And his eagerness to leave
his mother's womb

764
01:05:13,643 --> 01:05:16,144
was the very reason he was the one
who was selected.

765
01:05:16,229 --> 01:05:18,939
Ln competition
with five other unwanted pregnancies,

766
01:05:19,023 --> 01:05:21,817
the casting of a show,
determined by an air date,

767
01:05:21,943 --> 01:05:24,236
Truman was the one who
arrived on cue.

768
01:05:29,033 --> 01:05:31,910
Lncidentally, I believe
Truman is the first child

769
01:05:31,995 --> 01:05:34,496
to have been legally adopted
by a corporation.

770
01:05:34,580 --> 01:05:35,706
That's correct.

771
01:05:35,790 --> 01:05:38,166
The show has generated
enormous revenues,

772
01:05:38,251 --> 01:05:41,503
now equivalent to the gross national
product of a small country.

773
01:05:41,587 --> 01:05:42,754
People forget it takes

774
01:05:42,839 --> 01:05:45,549
the population of an entire country
to keep the show running.

775
01:05:45,633 --> 01:05:49,302
Since the show is on 24 hours a day
without commercial interruption,

776
01:05:49,387 --> 01:05:52,931
all those staggering revenues
are generated by product placement.

777
01:05:53,349 --> 01:05:55,684
That's true.
Everything on the show is for sale.

778
01:05:55,768 --> 01:05:59,062
From the actors' wardrobe, food
products, to the very homes they live in.

779
01:05:59,147 --> 01:06:01,481
All of it available in the Truman catalog

780
01:06:01,566 --> 01:06:02,941
and operators are standing by.

781
01:06:03,026 --> 01:06:04,776
Christof, let me ask you.

782
01:06:05,194 --> 01:06:08,447
Why do you think
that Truman has never come close

783
01:06:08,948 --> 01:06:12,075
to discovering the true nature
of his world until now?

784
01:06:12,535 --> 01:06:15,579
We accept the reality of the world
with which we are presented.

785
01:06:15,663 --> 01:06:17,289
Lt's as simple as that.

786
01:06:17,915 --> 01:06:19,541
The Hague for Christof.

787
01:06:19,625 --> 01:06:21,835
Hello? The Hague?

788
01:06:23,337 --> 01:06:26,923
All right, we've lost that call. Let's go
to Hollywood. You're on Trutalk.

789
01:06:27,008 --> 01:06:29,634
Hi, l'd just like to say one thing.

790
01:06:29,719 --> 01:06:31,386
You're a liar and a manipulator.

791
01:06:31,471 --> 01:06:33,764
And what you've done to Truman
is sick.

792
01:06:35,308 --> 01:06:37,434
We remember this voice, don't we?

793
01:06:38,686 --> 01:06:41,188
- How could we forget?
- Let's go to another call.

794
01:06:41,272 --> 01:06:44,566
No. lt's fine, Mike.

795
01:06:44,984 --> 01:06:47,903
L love to reminisce
with former members of the cast.

796
01:06:49,155 --> 01:06:50,405
Sylvia,

797
01:06:51,365 --> 01:06:54,201
as you announced
so melodramatically to the world,

798
01:06:55,495 --> 01:06:58,747
you think because you batted your eyes
at Truman once,

799
01:07:00,124 --> 01:07:01,583
flirted with him,

800
01:07:01,918 --> 01:07:04,211
stole a few minutes of airtime with him

801
01:07:04,295 --> 01:07:07,464
to thrust yourself and your politics
into the limelight,

802
01:07:07,548 --> 01:07:11,259
that you know him?
That you know what's right for him?

803
01:07:11,761 --> 01:07:14,387
You really think you're in a position
to judge him?

804
01:07:14,472 --> 01:07:16,598
What right do you have to take a baby

805
01:07:16,682 --> 01:07:19,351
and turn his life
into some kind of mockery?

806
01:07:20,186 --> 01:07:21,978
Don't you ever feel guilty?

807
01:07:23,648 --> 01:07:27,400
L have given Truman a chance
to lead a normal life.

808
01:07:28,736 --> 01:07:31,780
The world, the place you live in,

809
01:07:32,865 --> 01:07:34,282
is the sick place.

810
01:07:36,410 --> 01:07:38,453
Seahaven is the way
the world should be.

811
01:07:38,538 --> 01:07:42,249
He's not a performer. He's a prisoner.
Look at what you've done to him!

812
01:07:42,333 --> 01:07:44,042
He could leave at any time.

813
01:07:44,252 --> 01:07:46,795
Lf his was more than
just a vague ambition,

814
01:07:46,879 --> 01:07:50,465
if he was absolutely determined
to discover the truth,

815
01:07:51,676 --> 01:07:53,885
there's no way we could prevent him.

816
01:07:54,178 --> 01:07:56,847
L think what distresses you,

817
01:07:57,807 --> 01:08:01,059
really, caller, is that ultimately

818
01:08:02,311 --> 01:08:05,939
Truman prefers his cell, as you call it.

819
01:08:06,357 --> 01:08:08,066
That's where you're wrong.

820
01:08:08,568 --> 01:08:11,319
You're so wrong,
and he'll prove you wrong.

821
01:08:11,737 --> 01:08:15,949
Aside from the heated comments
of a very vocal minority,

822
01:08:16,159 --> 01:08:18,869
it's been
an overwhelmingly positive experience.

823
01:08:19,078 --> 01:08:21,413
Yes. For Truman
and for the viewing public.

824
01:08:21,497 --> 01:08:23,415
Christof, I can't thank you enough

825
01:08:23,499 --> 01:08:25,959
for giving so generously
of your time tonight.

826
01:08:26,043 --> 01:08:28,920
L think it's safe to say that
now that this crisis is behind us

827
01:08:29,005 --> 01:08:30,672
and that Truman's back to his old self,

828
01:08:30,756 --> 01:08:34,092
we can look forward
to some exciting new developments.

829
01:08:34,177 --> 01:08:37,512
Mike, the big news is
that Meryl will be leaving Truman

830
01:08:37,597 --> 01:08:39,181
in an upcoming episode.

831
01:08:39,265 --> 01:08:41,933
And a new romantic interest
will be introduced.

832
01:08:42,602 --> 01:08:46,938
L'm determined that television's first
on-air conception will still take place.

833
01:08:47,356 --> 01:08:51,359
Another television milestone
straight ahead. You heard it here first.

834
01:08:51,444 --> 01:08:54,196
Lt has been a singular honor
and a pleasure, sir.

835
01:08:54,280 --> 01:08:56,865
- Christof, thank you.
- Thank you, Mike.

836
01:10:15,319 --> 01:10:16,945
- Simeon.
- What?

837
01:10:21,367 --> 01:10:22,909
Ls he looking at us?

838
01:10:23,327 --> 01:10:25,287
Jesus, do you think he knows?

839
01:10:26,706 --> 01:10:27,706
Hello?

840
01:10:28,207 --> 01:10:29,749
Better call Christof.

841
01:10:29,875 --> 01:10:31,876
Hello? Come in, Major Burbank.

842
01:10:44,056 --> 01:10:45,056
Jesus.

843
01:10:49,395 --> 01:10:52,314
- He's back to his old self.
- Thank God.

844
01:11:00,156 --> 01:11:02,615
That's an unusual cat, my man.

845
01:11:07,496 --> 01:11:10,749
L hereby proclaim this planet...

846
01:11:15,504 --> 01:11:18,298
Trumania of the Burbank galaxy.

847
01:11:20,760 --> 01:11:23,094
- ls he gonna go?
- Okay, hallway camera ready.

848
01:11:24,972 --> 01:11:26,348
That one's for free.

849
01:11:26,432 --> 01:11:28,391
Keep up with him,
'cause he'll move fast.

850
01:11:28,476 --> 01:11:30,602
Stand by, all house cameras.

851
01:11:31,645 --> 01:11:33,855
- Morning!
- Good morning.

852
01:11:34,023 --> 01:11:35,690
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

853
01:11:35,775 --> 01:11:37,442
Ln case I don't see you...

854
01:11:37,526 --> 01:11:40,070
Good afternoon, good evening,
and good night.

855
01:11:42,490 --> 01:11:44,866
- Good afternoon...
- Good morning.

856
01:11:44,950 --> 01:11:47,077
Evening and good night.

857
01:11:47,745 --> 01:11:49,871
- Morning, Truman.
- Morning, Spencer.

858
01:11:49,955 --> 01:11:52,248
- How's it going?
- Let me check.

859
01:11:53,042 --> 01:11:54,584
Vital signs are good.

860
01:11:56,962 --> 01:11:58,213
Pluto!

861
01:11:58,756 --> 01:12:00,382
Good morning, Truman.

862
01:12:00,466 --> 01:12:03,218
- Look who's here.
- Beautiful day, isn't it?

863
01:12:03,511 --> 01:12:04,636
Every single day.

864
01:12:04,720 --> 01:12:07,639
The policy, we've thought about it
and we're gonna take it.

865
01:12:07,723 --> 01:12:09,015
- You're kidding?
- No!

866
01:12:09,100 --> 01:12:11,851
Why don't we go up to my office
right now and we'll sign the papers?

867
01:12:11,936 --> 01:12:14,562
Next week would be much better.

868
01:12:14,647 --> 01:12:17,857
- All right. See you guys.
- Okay, bye now. See you next week.

869
01:12:17,942 --> 01:12:20,610
- Give me something to look forward to.
- You got it.

870
01:12:20,694 --> 01:12:22,404
See, this isn't about insurance.

871
01:12:22,822 --> 01:12:26,991
This is about the great variable:
when will death occur?

872
01:12:27,326 --> 01:12:29,411
Could be a week, a month, a year.

873
01:12:30,454 --> 01:12:31,704
Could be today.

874
01:12:33,958 --> 01:12:36,251
"Sunbather, minding his own business,

875
01:12:37,086 --> 01:12:40,171
"stabbed in the heart by the tip
of a runaway beach umbrella."

876
01:12:40,256 --> 01:12:42,799
No way to guard against
that kind of thing.

877
01:12:44,969 --> 01:12:46,428
Sorry, excuse me.

878
01:12:46,637 --> 01:12:48,930
Truman, this is Vivien.
Vivien, this is Truman.

879
01:12:49,014 --> 01:12:51,349
The two of you are gonna be neighbors.

880
01:12:55,438 --> 01:12:59,149
L guess what l'm saying is that life is

881
01:12:59,942 --> 01:13:01,192
fragile.

882
01:13:02,945 --> 01:13:04,571
- Vivien, your office.
- Sorry.

883
01:13:04,655 --> 01:13:07,699
What's that? l'm sorry.

884
01:13:08,742 --> 01:13:09,868
You do?

885
01:13:10,744 --> 01:13:13,705
Great. Let me take your information.

886
01:13:30,014 --> 01:13:31,639
Ready, 2. Go to 2.

887
01:13:36,103 --> 01:13:37,562
And back to medium.

888
01:13:39,607 --> 01:13:40,982
And wide.

889
01:13:48,991 --> 01:13:51,743
L was just trying to train the kid to...

890
01:13:52,661 --> 01:13:53,995
Never mind.

891
01:13:57,208 --> 01:13:59,250
What's he doing in the basement?

892
01:13:59,543 --> 01:14:02,045
He moved down there
after Meryl packed up and left.

893
01:14:02,129 --> 01:14:03,546
Why wasn't I told?

894
01:14:03,631 --> 01:14:06,257
Any unpredictable behavior
has to be reported.

895
01:14:07,676 --> 01:14:09,552
He's just sleeping, I thought.

896
01:14:09,637 --> 01:14:12,180
- This the best shot we've got?
- What's to see?

897
01:14:12,264 --> 01:14:15,892
- What's on the clock cam?
- Lt's an obstruction.

898
01:14:16,393 --> 01:14:20,146
- What happened down there?
- He was just tidying up his garbage.

899
01:14:21,148 --> 01:14:25,109
L was gonna call you, but halfway
through, he gave up, and he fell asleep.

900
01:14:25,486 --> 01:14:28,655
L wanna check on the setups
for the insurance convention tomorrow.

901
01:14:28,739 --> 01:14:30,114
- Yes.
- Yeah.

902
01:14:31,116 --> 01:14:32,450
Nice move.

903
01:14:41,544 --> 01:14:42,794
There you go.

904
01:14:53,764 --> 01:14:55,139
Lsolate the audio.

905
01:14:56,475 --> 01:14:58,476
Give me a close-up on his torso.

906
01:15:01,313 --> 01:15:02,814
He's still breathing.

907
01:15:05,025 --> 01:15:06,693
Where's Chloe? Call him.

908
01:15:06,902 --> 01:15:10,154
- What do you want me to say?
- Tell him it's a wrong number.

909
01:15:13,617 --> 01:15:15,201
What took you so long?

910
01:15:15,661 --> 01:15:18,204
Just had to wait for it. They were busy.

911
01:15:19,123 --> 01:15:21,541
Here. What's going on?

912
01:15:22,376 --> 01:15:24,127
L don't know. They're...

913
01:15:24,295 --> 01:15:27,255
He came down into the room. He did
nothing but stand around for a while.

914
01:15:27,339 --> 01:15:28,840
Shut up and watch it.

915
01:15:29,466 --> 01:15:31,551
Then we went to night vision.

916
01:15:32,344 --> 01:15:33,761
He's asleep.

917
01:15:35,389 --> 01:15:36,639
- There!
- What?

918
01:15:37,057 --> 01:15:38,808
- Zoom in.
- On which?

919
01:15:39,143 --> 01:15:40,727
Under the chair there.

920
01:15:43,188 --> 01:15:44,522
Enhance it.

921
01:15:47,067 --> 01:15:49,569
- ls it...
- My God.

922
01:15:51,363 --> 01:15:54,490
He couldn't have gone up the stairs.
He must still be in the room.

923
01:15:54,575 --> 01:15:56,200
- Get Marlon over there.
- Right away.

924
01:16:11,884 --> 01:16:13,051
Truman!

925
01:16:13,927 --> 01:16:15,219
Surprise party!

926
01:16:17,264 --> 01:16:18,556
Come on, buddy.

927
01:16:18,807 --> 01:16:21,934
L got a six-pack of cold brewskis
with our name on them.

928
01:16:22,061 --> 01:16:24,354
Come on, pal. Come on, buddy.

929
01:16:28,359 --> 01:16:29,442
Shit.

930
01:16:32,738 --> 01:16:35,239
Marlon, find him. He's still in the room.

931
01:16:39,620 --> 01:16:41,537
Come out, come out, wherever you are.

932
01:16:41,622 --> 01:16:43,414
That's good. Keep it light.

933
01:16:44,333 --> 01:16:46,793
L know you're in here.
L'm gonna find you.

934
01:16:50,381 --> 01:16:51,964
Check under the table.

935
01:16:53,384 --> 01:16:55,009
The closet, behind you.

936
01:16:59,014 --> 01:17:00,014
Huh.

937
01:17:01,809 --> 01:17:02,809
Gee.

938
01:17:03,686 --> 01:17:05,895
L wonder where he could possibly be.

939
01:17:13,821 --> 01:17:16,072
The lawn cam, get me the lawn cam.

940
01:17:23,747 --> 01:17:26,416
Don't look in the camera.
Say something. Keep it going.

941
01:17:26,500 --> 01:17:27,625
He's gone.

942
01:17:28,127 --> 01:17:29,961
- Cut transmission!
- Cut transmission?

943
01:17:30,045 --> 01:17:31,295
Cut it!

944
01:17:33,674 --> 01:17:35,550
Jesus! God in heaven!

945
01:17:37,136 --> 01:17:39,470
- Everything's black.
- Give me the phone.

946
01:17:52,317 --> 01:17:54,527
L don't know where he is, but he's gone.

947
01:18:00,909 --> 01:18:03,995
All right. We've got
every available extra looking for him.

948
01:18:04,079 --> 01:18:08,374
The principals are helping out. The
crew, too. So every sector's covered.

949
01:18:09,042 --> 01:18:11,753
- What about prop cars?
- Yes, they've been accounted for.

950
01:18:11,837 --> 01:18:13,254
He has to be on foot.

951
01:18:13,338 --> 01:18:16,257
He has the world's most
recognizable face. He can't disappear.

952
01:18:52,127 --> 01:18:53,211
Go.

953
01:18:54,087 --> 01:18:57,715
Hunt him. Yeah. Go find him, Pluto.

954
01:18:58,300 --> 01:18:59,509
Good dog!

955
01:18:59,593 --> 01:19:00,843
All this fuss.

956
01:19:01,678 --> 01:19:03,679
Lf he could just hear my voice.

957
01:19:04,640 --> 01:19:05,848
Truman!

958
01:19:08,977 --> 01:19:11,270
Let me try. Truman!

959
01:19:12,564 --> 01:19:14,398
Lt's me, Dad!

960
01:19:16,693 --> 01:19:17,902
Let's talk.

961
01:19:19,571 --> 01:19:21,072
Yeah, I know.

962
01:19:22,783 --> 01:19:24,700
Just about done with the square.

963
01:19:24,785 --> 01:19:27,370
Got to go back to Barrymore,
check the interiors.

964
01:19:27,454 --> 01:19:29,664
- He's got to be in there.
- Barrymore.

965
01:19:30,082 --> 01:19:32,208
But what about the college?
Who's watching that?

966
01:19:32,292 --> 01:19:33,292
L don't know.

967
01:19:33,377 --> 01:19:35,711
- Send somebody over there, okay?
- All right.

968
01:19:39,967 --> 01:19:42,343
Take another man
and get down there now, all right?

969
01:19:42,427 --> 01:19:44,679
L don't give a damn.
Just find the son of a bitch.

970
01:19:44,763 --> 01:19:45,721
Get some batteries.

971
01:19:45,806 --> 01:19:48,516
This guy's not gonna glow in the dark.
Get them down here.

972
01:19:48,600 --> 01:19:51,310
L don't know what's going on.
Reroute it back to me.

973
01:19:51,395 --> 01:19:54,605
We need more light.
We'll never find him this way.

974
01:19:59,903 --> 01:20:01,279
What time is it?

975
01:20:01,613 --> 01:20:03,906
Lt's way too early for that.

976
01:20:10,622 --> 01:20:11,789
Cue the sun.

977
01:20:18,380 --> 01:20:19,755
What time is it?

978
01:20:20,757 --> 01:20:22,466
Christof, what's going on?

979
01:20:23,010 --> 01:20:25,970
Did you know there's a rumor
circulating that he's dead?

980
01:20:26,054 --> 01:20:27,221
You hear me?

981
01:20:27,306 --> 01:20:29,599
The media is having a feeding frenzy
over this.

982
01:20:29,683 --> 01:20:31,434
All the phone lines are jammed,

983
01:20:31,518 --> 01:20:33,102
and every network has a pirated shot

984
01:20:33,186 --> 01:20:35,467
of Marlon making an ass of himself
in front of the camera.

985
01:20:35,522 --> 01:20:37,732
The sponsors are threatening
to rip up their contracts.

986
01:20:37,816 --> 01:20:39,233
Why? We're getting higher ratings
with this graphic

987
01:20:39,318 --> 01:20:42,403
than we've ever had on this show.

988
01:20:45,324 --> 01:20:46,616
No sign of him.

989
01:20:46,783 --> 01:20:49,577
Marlon, why don't you head back to town
and join the others?

990
01:20:49,661 --> 01:20:52,622
Everyone else is at first positions, okay?
Thank you.

991
01:20:54,166 --> 01:20:56,375
Everyone's at first positions, right?

992
01:21:11,767 --> 01:21:15,269
We've got the light.
So he's got to be there somewhere.

993
01:21:18,065 --> 01:21:19,774
We're not watching the sea.

994
01:21:19,858 --> 01:21:22,401
Hang on a minute.
Why would we watch the sea?

995
01:21:23,028 --> 01:21:24,362
